'''Aubrey Morgan O'Day''' (born February 11, 1984) is an American singer and reality television personality who has been a member of the [[girl group]] [[Danity Kane]]. Following discord among Danity Kane and with her mentor at the time, [[Sean Combs|P. Diddy]], O'Day was fired from the group in 2008,<ref name="news.bostonherald.com">{{cite news |title=Aubrey O'Day swears she's not Donnie Wahlberg's girl – honest!| newspaper=[[Boston Herald]]|date=October 9, 2008 |access-date=October 9, 2008 |url= http://news.bostonherald.com/track/inside_track/view/2008_10_09_Aubrey_O_Day_laughing_over_Donnie_Wahlberg_dating_rumors!/srvc=home&position=also}}</ref> but reunited with them in 2013 before a second disbandment. Danity Kane reunited in 2018 as a trio. She also performed in the duo [[Dumblonde]] with former Danity Kane bandmate [[Shannon Bex]] from 2015 to 2019.

O'Day has modeled for magazines such as ''[[Blender (magazine)|Blender]]'' and ''[[Playboy]]'', and performed on [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] in ''[[Hairspray (musical)|Hairspray]]''. In 2011, she signed a solo record deal with SRC/[[Universal Motown Records]], and released her debut EP ''[[Between Two Evils]]'' in 2013.

Additionally, O'Day has made appearances on reality television shows, including the fifth season of ''[[The Celebrity Apprentice 5|Celebrity Apprentice]]'', ''[[Famously Single]]'', ''[[Ex on the Beach (American TV series)|Ex on the Beach]]'', the British ''[[Celebrity Big Brother (British series 18)|Celebrity Big Brother 18]]'', and [[The Masked Singer (American TV series)|The Masked Singer]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radiotimes.com/news/2016-07-28/who-is-aubrey-oday-celebrity-big-brother-2016-contestant-guide |title=Aubrey O'Day: CBB line up 2016 – guide to the Making the Band singer |publisher=Radiotimes.com |date=July 28, 2016 |access-date=August 2, 2016}}</ref>

==Early life==
O'Day began performing at age five. "I lived on the stage, and even at six, slept behind the seats of the theatre", she stated in an interview.<ref name="www.aubreyoday.com">{{cite web|title=Aubrey O'Day|publisher=aubreyoday.com|url=http://www.aubreyoday.com}}</ref> According to her mother, when O'Day was four, she was at a performance of ''[[The Nutcracker]]'' and started to cry. Her mother asked her what was wrong and O'Day replied, "I'm sad that I'm sitting here and not up on stage." O'Day recalls that moment as the one in which she "officially" realized her love for entertainment.<ref name="www.aubreyoday.com"/>

O'Day played lead characters in various musical productions, including Dorothy in ''[[The Wonderful Wizard of Oz|The Wizard of Oz]]'', Carmen in ''[[Fame (musical)|Fame]]'', Sandy in ''[[Grease (musical)|Grease]]'',<ref name="blender.com">{{cite magazine|title=Aubrey O'Day MTV's Making the Band hottie gears up for more catfights and dance-offs.|magazine=[[Blender (magazine)|Blender]]|date=September 2005|access-date=October 16, 2008|url=http://www.blender.com/guide/articles.aspx?id=1726|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081019014111/http://www.blender.com/guide/articles.aspx?id=1726|archive-date=October 19, 2008|url-status=dead}}</ref> Liesl in ''[[The Sound of Music]]'', Tzeitel in ''[[Fiddler on the Roof]]'', and Mimi in ''[[Rent (musical)|Rent]]''. She also appeared in ''[[Annie (musical)|Annie]]''.<ref name="blender.com"/> O'Day's childhood leaned heavily toward auditions and acting gigs more than school.<ref>"I never really went to school," she joked. "I was in and out of auditioning." quoted in Blender Magazine</ref> [[The Notorious B.I.G.]], [[Sean Combs|Sean "Puffy" Combs]], [[Lauryn Hill]], [[Janet Jackson]] and [[Christina Aguilera]] were her primary influences growing up.<ref name="blender.com"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.papermag.com/dumblonde-bianca#rebelltitem28/ |title= Dumblonde Discovers Their Light |publisher= Paper |date=April 22, 2019 |access-date= April 22, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://thatgrapejuice.net/2011/04/grape-juice-interviews-au

